      <h5> Set Up Procedure</h5>

      <div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert">
            <strong>0. </strong>Create a free heroku here: https://signup.heroku.com/
        </div>


      <div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert">
          <strong>1. </strong> Install (or upgrade) to the latest LTS version of nodeJS (Google how to)
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>2. </strong>Install git, use this: https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-Installing-Git
      </div>

      <div id = "stamp" class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>3. </strong>Open a directory of your choice (where your project will reside) in the terminal
      </div>

      <div  class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>4. </strong>Clone my repo, run git clone https://github.com/Anyungu/node-sigfox-warefab-api.git in your folder
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>4. </strong> go into the newly cloned folder called node-sigfox-warefab-api
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>5. </strong> run npm install (install all the packages)
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>6. </strong> run npm start (test if its running on localhost, if not you are most likely using an old nodeJS)
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>7. </strong> http://localhost:9200/, App Should be running here
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>8. </strong> run git init (initialize a repo), git add . (add files to cache)
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>9. </strong> run git init (initialize a repo), git add . (add files to cache)
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>10. </strong> Install heroku Cli. Use this https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/heroku-cli
      </div>


      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>10. </strong> run heroku login, heroku create {prefered-name-of-your-app}, mine is ltk-warefab
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>10. </strong> run git push heroku master
      </div>

      <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
            <strong>10. </strong> run heroku open, and view your App
      </div>



      
      


     
